{
  "article_id": "DailyNewsAndIndependent1916",
  "paragraphs": [
    [
      {
        "text": "Crawfish are disappearing from the waters about the "
      },
      {
        "text": "channel islands",
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", and according to the observations of "
      },
      {
        "text": "George Nidever",
        "entity_key": "gnijr",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "the \"sheephejad\" [sheephead] a species of fish, is the cause. This ravenous fish is said to be making rapid inroads upon both crawfish and lobsters."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Mr. Nidever",
        "entity_key": "gnijr",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "has a crawfish camp on the ocean side of "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Cruz island",
        "entity_key": "i_scruz",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". He has just come to "
      },
      {
        "text": "the mainland",
        "entity_key": "re_mld",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "to visit relatives and prepare for other activities. He says the past season has been a hard one for lobster fishers. He has gone to many fathoms with his traps in an effort to keep up with the market demands for crawfish."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "In many of his traps he has found fat sheephead fast prisoners. They [p]oked their heads into traps after the lobster bait, and many, not being able to escape, were hauled to the surface. \"They are eating tons and tons of the young lobsters,\" said "
      },
      {
        "text": "Mr. Nidever",
        "entity_key": "gnijr",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", \"and within a few years there will not be a lobster remaining.' [sic]"
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Mr. Nidever",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "gnijr",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "is a son of ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Captain Nidever",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", who attained historical fame in [t]hese parts by rescuing from ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the islands",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "the ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "last remaining member",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "of ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "a tribe of Indians",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "which once lived there.",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "An "
      },
      {
        "text": "Indian woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "had been left behind by accident when "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Indians",
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "were brought to "
      },
      {
        "text": "the mainland",
        "entity_key": "re_mld",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", and years later "
      },
      {
        "text": "Captain Nidever",
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "discovered her tracks in the beach sands, and led an expedition to rescue her."
